</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA1DED014E16FFE1FF59FC03FACD221F" blockId="7.[151,1437,906,1903]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FF59FC03FE3E26D2" author="Callaghan" box="[151,456,906,931]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Nobre, C. E. B (2014) A new species of Pheles Herrich - Schaeffer from Northeast Brazil (Lepidoptera, Riodinidae). Zootaxa, 3780, 558 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3780.3.7" type="journal article" year="2014">
Callaghan &amp; Nobre (
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FE4BFC02FE3626D2" box="[389,448,907,931]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
expressed their doubts about the generic placement of this recently described species, indicating a number of divergent characters from those observed in typical 
<taxonomicName id="7DA296824E16FFE1FBC5FC27FBA026B6" box="[1035,1110,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Pheles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88D631134E16FFE1FBC5FC27FBA026B6" box="[1035,1110,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Pheles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, 
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FAC4FC27FED8269A" author="Callaghan" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Nobre, C. E. B (2014) A new species of Pheles Herrich - Schaeffer from Northeast Brazil (Lepidoptera, Riodinidae). Zootaxa, 3780, 558 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3780.3.7" type="journal article" year="2014">
Callaghan &amp; Nobre (
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FF25FC5AFED0269A" box="[235,294,979,1003]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
provisionally described this species in 
<taxonomicName id="7DA296824E16FFE1FD2DFC5BFCD8269A" box="[739,814,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Pheles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88D631134E16FFE1FD2DFC5BFCD8269A" box="[739,814,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Pheles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until its proper generic placement could be ascertained. Closer examination reveals several characters that support its placement in 
<taxonomicName id="7DA296824E16FFE1FC26FC7FFB56217E" authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" box="[1000,1184,1014,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Melanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88D631134E16FFE1FC26FC7FFBB4217E" box="[1000,1090,1014,1039]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Melanis</emphasis>
Hübner
</taxonomicName>
, [
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FB7DFC7EFB04217E" box="[1203,1266,1015,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="1819.0">1819</number>
], as defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FF59FB93FEC22142" author="Stichel" box="[151,308,1050,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Stichel, H. F. E. J. (1911) Fam. Riodinidae. Allgemeines - Subfam. Riodininae. Genera Insectorum, 112 B, 239 - 452." type="journal article" year="1911">
Stichel (
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FF3DFB92FEDA2142" box="[243,300,1051,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="1911.0">1911</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
(
<emphasis id="88D631134E16FFE1FE8AFB95FE342142" box="[324,450,1052,1075]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">
i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="7DA296824E16FFE1FEA2FB95FE342142" authority="Blanchard, 1840 sensu Stichel (1911)" authorityName="Blanchard, 1840 sensu Stichel" authorityYear="1911" box="[364,450,1052,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Lymnas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lymnas</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Blanchard, 
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FD84FB92FD742142" box="[586,642,1051,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="1840.0">1840</number>
<emphasis id="88D631134E16FFE1FD47FB95FD312142" box="[649,711,1052,1075]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FD03FB93FC982142" author="Stichel" box="[717,878,1050,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Stichel, H. F. E. J. (1911) Fam. Riodinidae. Allgemeines - Subfam. Riodininae. Genera Insectorum, 112 B, 239 - 452." type="journal article" year="1911">
Stichel (
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FCE4FB92FC902142" box="[810,870,1051,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="1911.0">1911</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
; see 
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FC6DFB93FB872142" author="Hemming" box="[931,1137,1050,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Hemming, A. F. (1967) The generic names of the butterflies and their type - species (Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera). Bulletin of the British Museum of natural History (Entomology), 9 (Supplement), 1 - 509." type="journal article" year="1967">
Hemming (
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FBECFB93FBA82142" box="[1058,1118,1050,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="1967.0">1967</number>
))
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FBB5FB93FAEE2142" author="Stichel" box="[1147,1304,1050,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Stichel, H. F. E. J. (1911) Fam. Riodinidae. Allgemeines - Subfam. Riodininae. Genera Insectorum, 112 B, 239 - 452." type="journal article" year="1911">
Stichel (
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FB19FB92FAE62142" box="[1239,1296,1051,1075]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="1911.0">1911</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
divided the genus in two sections and a number of cohorts, and he noted that the general conformation of the male genitalia is similar among them, differing only in specific characters. These characters includes the ventral arm of the tegumen dorsally horizontal and projected anteriorly, connecting ventrally to the strap–like saccus (“L–shaped vinculum” 
<emphasis id="88D631134E16FFE1FF59FB25FF2321B2" box="[151,213,1196,1219]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FF2FFB23FDE621B2" author="Callaghan" box="[225,528,1194,1219]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Nobre, C. E. B (2014) A new species of Pheles Herrich - Schaeffer from Northeast Brazil (Lepidoptera, Riodinidae). Zootaxa, 3780, 558 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3780.3.7" type="journal article" year="2014">
Callaghan &amp; Nobre 
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FE1DFB22FDE621B2" box="[467,528,1195,1219]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); valve comparatively very large, ventrally tapering to a point and projected dorsally; transtilla developed and lobed; and aedeagus strongly curved ventrally and posteriorly tapering to a point, with the anterior end enlarged and bulbous. The shape of the distal end of the fultura inferior, described by 
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FF59FA9FFE3D205E" author="Callaghan" box="[151,459,1302,1327]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Nobre, C. E. B (2014) A new species of Pheles Herrich - Schaeffer from Northeast Brazil (Lepidoptera, Riodinidae). Zootaxa, 3780, 558 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3780.3.7" type="journal article" year="2014">
Callaghan &amp; Nobre (
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FE46FA9EFE35205E" box="[392,451,1303,1327]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as a “fork serving as a guide for the aedeagus”, were described by 
<bibRefCitation id="DE3390F04E16FFE1FB15FA9FFA8D205E" author="Stichel" box="[1243,1403,1302,1327]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" refString="Stichel, H. F. E. J. (1911) Fam. Riodinidae. Allgemeines - Subfam. Riodininae. Genera Insectorum, 112 B, 239 - 452." type="journal article" year="1911">
Stichel (
<number id="0C6AFF264E16FFE1FAF4FA9EFA85205E" box="[1338,1395,1303,1327]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" value="1911.0">1911</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as “saddle–shaped” (“Sattelförmig” and “Selle” 
<emphasis id="88D631134E16FFE1FD57FAB5FD212022" box="[665,727,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">sensu</emphasis>
