</taxonomicName>
. In females, the ductus bursae sclerotized near to the ostium, the pear-shaped corpus bursae and the slit-shaped signa, one dorsal and other ventral, also occurs in 
<taxonomicName id="7DA296824E16FFE1FBD8FA0BFB8620EA" box="[1046,1136,1410,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Melanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88D631134E16FFE1FBD8FA0BFB8620EA" box="[1046,1136,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Melanis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
